510
00:37:48,660 --> 00:37:50,940
<i>Not picking up.</i> <i>Or returning messages or texts.</i>

511
00:37:50,940 --> 00:37:53,610
We're on our own here, so just give me some theories we can use.

512
00:37:55,060 --> 00:37:56,980
Hematologic malignancies.

513
00:37:56,980 --> 00:37:59,830
A- T patients are more prone to that form of cancer.

514
00:37:59,830 --> 00:38:03,300
You think cancer would present <i>and kill her in three days?</i>

515
00:38:04,560 --> 00:38:06,160
Not cancer.

516
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:08,850
But a tumor could act like a clot.

517
00:38:08,850 --> 00:38:11,040
An atrial myxoma.

518
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,930
A primary heart tumor.

519
00:38:14,930 --> 00:38:19,390
The swinging motion of the myxoma intermittently blocked the flow of blood through the right atrium.

520
00:38:19,390 --> 00:38:23,910
Inflow blockage stagnated the hepatic vein, which clotted and caused liver failure.

521
00:38:23,910 --> 00:38:27,250
Outflow blockage caused the Raynaud's phenomenon and stroke.

522
00:38:27,250 --> 00:38:29,860
Pieces of the tumor broke off and lodged in the lungs,

523
00:38:29,860 --> 00:38:32,860
<i>causing Emily's breathing problems</i> <i>and the coughing blood.</i>

524
00:38:32,860 --> 00:38:37,600
We'll remove the tumor surgically, and hopefully the biopsy reveals it's benign.

525
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:19,120
Wow. You-
you really look like crap.

